OL,3,CD-Day 80 The Last Veterans: Mary Holley
OL,5,F"And only people who lived or worked
OL,6,Fthere could go. We all suspected. I
OL,7,Fknew he was on Frobisher, I knew she
OL,8,Fwas a cruiser so she would have been
OL,9,Fup in the forefront.
OL,11,F"They were in the bombardment of Gold
OL,12,FBeach each and it must have worked
OL,13,Fbecause he was one of the signalmen
OL,14,Fsent ashore. I don't know how,
OL,15,Fpresumably by tender. To set up a
OL,16,Fsignal station on the beach.
OL,18,F"It must of been after that that she
OL,19,Fwas torpedoed.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G3/7
